                                    <div class="slide slide_1">
                                        <div class="slide-content">
                                            <h2>Education</h2>
                                            <p>In 2017, I graduated from elementary school in Canmaya Centro, Sagbayan, Bohol.
                                            I pursued my secondary education at San Agustin National High School and took up Humanities and Social Sciences as a strand in Senior High School.
                                            Fastforward to tertiary education and I am currently burning a candle at both ends as I enrolled myself to Bachelor of Secondary Education major in Information Technology
                                            at University of Cebu Lapu-Lapu and Mandaue Campus.

                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                    
                                    <div class="slide slide_2">
                                        <div class="slide-content">
                                            <h2>Childhood</h2>
                                            <p>I grew up in a small town in Canmaya Centro, Sagbayan, Bohol where I was surrounded with caves that have echoed unknown voices, cows that would mock every passers by with thier loud moo,
                                            hills that cleared away our emotional outburst as me and my friends raced to the top, woods that beckoned us to explore its uncharted paths buried
                                            deep under dead leaves, and rivers that are not only home to exotic piscatorial creatures but had also pulled in innocent famished bodies. Growing up
                                            I was in awe with how a little barangay could encapsulate such abundant and magnificent natural resources that hid dark stories meant to be burned in the past. But,
                                            on top of it all, I was brought up into an environment with people whose bond are strong than of those people living in cities.
                                            The townspeople helped one another in their daily predicaments allowing them to navigate their way through life's challenges and live in harmonious melody.
                                            The characteristics and perspective that I now possess are credited to my hometown.
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                    
                                    <div class="slide slide_3">
                                        <div class="slide-content">
                                            <h2>Hobbies</h2>
                                            <p>I have always been fond of watching movies since I was little. I would save up my weekly allowance of 25 pesos when I was in elementary just buy
                                            a compact disk of my favorite movies and I would lock myself from the outside world and immerse myself in different realms and spaces. Another hobby
                                            of mine is listening to a plethora of music genres. It has became a routine of mine to look up for good songs to blast in our House
                                            before I start doing certain tasks. Playing guitar was a hobby that I just recently unearthed withing myself. Its probably the result of being an avid music listener. However, everythiing is still work in progress and I am still doing my best to be proficient in playing the instrument.
                                            Reading books was another hobby that I enjoyed doing. My younger self who'd spend most of his times hanging out with his friends,
                                            frequently engaging in risk taking endeavors such as searching for rare kinds of spiders at night would never believe that his 16 year old self has taught himself to read.
                            
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                    
                                    <div class="slide slide_4">
                                        <div class="slide-content">
                                            <h2>Extracurriculars and Work Experiences</h2>
                                            <p>I was a contributor as well as a photojournalist in our school publication paper in SHS and I got to write several articles.<br><br>
                                                I got to work in a small retail store when I was 16 years old and I managed to develop my communication skills in that shortlasting job.<br><br>
                                                During summer vacation, I worked in our Municipal Hall where I was assigned at the Waterworks Systems Office. I got to enhance a lot of skills in that work with  a wide scope of duties.
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
